  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n@mentions in chat text input present various issues.\r\n## Description\r\n1) When mention is inserted and the mention text is edited and became invalid, the text is still formatted as if it was valid mention\r\n2) If mention is inserted and the @ is removed the text is still formatted as if it was valid mention\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n1) Add a mention and go back to the mention text with pressing the left arrow and either type any character or press space\r\n2) Add a mention and go back to the mention text with pressing the left arrow and delete the @ symbol\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1) The mention becomes invalid, the formatting is removed\r\n2) The mention becomes invalid, the formatting is removed\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1) The mention becomes invalid, the formatting stays as is\r\n2) The mention becomes invalid, the formatting stays as is\r\n3) using @ does not suggest any suggestions in public chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31625338/149036440-1d57d485-91a3-4823-b5d5-0f1cf7e67586.mov\r\nIn other chat applications, is generally not possible to go into the mention text, when a mention is in the text input and left or right buttons are pressed, the cursor just jumps over the mention text. Also mentions are inserted only when selecting a name from the popup list and not by just typing it.\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: master branch `70d58b4dceb6c3f5fb3de8ecdd95776e0f0b9f68`\r\n- Operating System: MacOS Big Sur\r\n\r\n",
